text: THIS IS NOT HOW THE SLENDERMAN WORKS!  Seriously, as a fan of MarbleHornets, EverymanHybrid, and the classic slender man mythos, this looks like the final nail in the coffin for Mr. Tall Dark and Faceless. It is certainly proof that the Slenderman has been overdone to the point of irrelevance if a big Hollywood studio is going to make a generic as hell movie connected only tangentially to the source material.  Part of me is genuinely curious if the studio execs even bothered to acquire film rights from Eric "Victor Surge" Knudsen to use his IP, or if they just assumed that because Slenderman was an internet meme that they could use it for free.  Same goes for the Slenderman fan art that is shown all over the trailer.

text: Ah yes, another worthless horror film that's bound to have piss poor actors, a shitty script, shitty character development and (above all) a shitty storyline. This film alone is bound to be another quick cash grab for Hollywood because sadly society can't see how pathetic we are. Horror use to have such a fantastic art form, tested the boundaries of cinema; and now (yet once again) we've embarrassed the art form of cinema horror. Horror was made to test the boundaries of film as a whole. It's why films such as Suspiria, Anti-Christ, Epidemic, The Exorcist, Sleep Away Camp, American Werewolf In London and The Shinning were so effective during their time. Anyone who even thinks this is gonna be good will surely regret their decision before the credits begin to roll. I can assure the lot of you that. This trailer probably ruined a good chunk of the film too.

text: OH BOI HERE COMES A RANT.  lemme explain for those who don't see how this movie will be awful, the fact of the matter is Slender Man hasn't been popular for years and won't be again because of this movie. It appears they're mostly going to make cheap references to the mythos and only dabble in what made the creature scary.   For those who believe he wasn't scary at all, cool, horror is subjective and is different from person to person but for many including myself the reason Slender Man was scary was the fact you did not know what he planned to do with you. You didn't know how he interacted with the world around him, you didn't know what he was doing or why. You didn't know, thats why he was scary!   He was a literal blank slate, a character to be filled, many media involving him (mostly webseries) took the concept and added their own spin. Marble Hornets named him the Operator and he manipulated people to spread his sickness to others. (I know to some this sounds generic, but it was the first coming out in 2009 right when he was created) another series TribeTwelve made his victims into vessels for other beings who work with him, toying with them as he did and was also named the Administrator. In everymanHYBRID the creature has control over the lives of 4 people who he constantly reincarnates only to mess with again.   My point is, this film chose to be so generic with the character and I believe this is the biggest issue, i would much rather see a film that chose to make their own version of the slender man while not straying too far from the original.

text: Ok multiple problems with this. One when you see him he takes you that's it you disappear like in the game and stories of creepypasta. Sure in one game or maybe more I've only played the first slenderman game and played the slenderman return game. On PC but then they put slenderman to playstation I remember something like that and had I think her name katey or just someone chase you and claw you in that. I'm guessing she was possessed or brainwashed been a while. Anyway, 2, slenderman...a virus. Ok I'm all up 4 new ideas for creatures to infect and cause insanity but when you have this character and have all the info at disposal and still don't use it is rather more frightening than this. 3, who the hell goes out to the woods for their friend at NIGHT I add. Yeah real smart all you'll find is, well someone already made the joke of this, a corpse, to that person I give credit. 4...i know being picky but last time I checked you find pages and then hear what sounds like distant fireworks from Disneyland. Basically loud drum boom sounds. Not bells. 5, you don't look at him if you do you get taken. 6 why jumpscares this character creature is more than jump scares. But no let's be lazy and do this. Ya know after this honestly I'm up for Hollywood movies to try and make something new and go different routes with things like with the deadpool movie didn't follow much comic wise just did it's own thing. But when it comes to this, and going about it first time with literally all info and don't really use much. feels rather lazy and little if not insulting to the character. Seeing how I still plan to see this to see how it might turn out my Hope's are low and I mean low. And if it is worse than it looks than I pray it will end this cause this is creepypasta and they managed to mess up from trailer point of view. Now if wish to argue please do cause I'm open to hear thoughts, perspective, and more knowledge to original source of slenderman and more abilities, from those who actually took time and effort to learn more of this and other creepypasta characters.

text: Way better than the first trailer, but my skepticism stands. I appreciate the use of his online origins as the means of discovery & summoning. I can't be too upset if it is primarily jumpscares, but to be honest, his video game history is just that. It seems like they're following the right path of adaptation while trying to build a narrative around it.  Besides, this is the perfect/appropriate time to make this movie considering his...past influences. My skepticism comes from whether this is a retread of classic horror movie mistakes such as uninteresting characters, giving the villain an absurd backstory it doesn't need, and setting up something bigger. I believe, especially with the roll horror movies have been on the past few years, Slender Man has the potential to stand out for good reasons...it's just a matter of how it's presented

text: Ok, if anyone sees this, this is what I think that the Slender Man movie should been.  The start where they're going through their friends computer and find the 'Slenderman Mythos' stuff is perfect.  The idea that they summon him to try and find their friend, instead of stupid college kids trying to be edgy'TM, is a good idea.  Where I think the movie will falter is that they'll make it so obvious that it's Slender, and lose the reason why the game, and other versions of him like The Operator from Marble Hornets, scary is the suspense.  Instead of having them obviously fighting a monster it should be a paranoi inducing film.  Slow builds and logical, more likely, answers to what happened.  The only times that 'The Slender Man' should appear is when they think that they're being chased and stalked.  The Slenderman game with the 8 pages worked because it was tense, you knew you were being stalked, but you didn't know where it was.  Replacing horror building suspense for tryharding jumpscares will not work, and I think that's what the movie is going to be like.  I hope that I'm wrong, but I think that the movie is going to miss nearly every mark.

text: Here, a much better plot idea, and please tell me what anyone thinks if they read it. You know it would have been better as an R rated movie with a detective looking for missing children, a town completely surrounded by woods, and children would go missing with barely a trace but a small note or sketch of Slenderman. Toensfolk and destrot parents describing a tall figure who would be in the distance, a man in a suit. The detective seeing what appears to be a figure in the woods with that description and what looks like a child holding his hand, only to see it was a tree with a doll and a note. In the end slender torments him through what appears to be an endless night as he is chased and attacked by him, trying to fight back but ending up snapping back to reality and seeing that the children were killed, surrounded by their bodies as the last thing we see and hear is slenders face and what sounds like a static scream as he attacks the victim, even if he lives, slender had broken him, he had made him see him until he goes crazy as the final scene is another victim to slender. Instead we get this cast that looks fresh off a Nickelodeon show trying to find their friend by going into the dark woods with nothing, after looking at what Slenderman was! Could have been better with the crappy characters if the movie had slender really fuck with their heads, thoughts of their friend dead, the forest seeming endless with no escape, something actually entertaining. Also the voice acting sucks!

text: Why does every horror monster need to have a bunch of dumb gimmicks? They just made up some super cheesy rules out of nowhere & expect people to find it scary. They should've leaned into the internet hoax aspect of Slenderman, make it ambiguous if he's even real. The unknown is scary because it's unknown, that's why everyone loves Lovecraft.  The best structure for this movie would be to do it in the vein of Blair Witch, have the main characters filming in the woods, trying to find the Scary Internet Monster, or he'll, maybe even have them try to stage pictures. Throw in the creepy atmosphere from the game with some ominous notes on trees, maybe some deranged fans of Slenderman to mimic those real life killings and Bam, you get a serviceable psychological thriller. It's not hard, they're just not trying.

text: Let me tell you all a story..   When i was in 2nd grade, i honestly thought slenderman was real. I was scared shitless about it. Drove me fucking insane. My closet was turned into a giant theory center, how to fend him off, how to stop him, what to do if he catches you. I saw things, hallucinations because of all the stress i went though. This shit went on until 4th grade. By then i had enough stuff about the long boi here that i could make a book. That was until i saw that one news report. About the 2 girls that stabbed their friend for him. I was shocked and terrified, but the one thing that iffed me.  *he wasnt real* I went insane, everything i studied, the hours i wasted, the YEARS. All for nothing. And so i burned all my work in a large bonfire. I was sad, but i became relieved. I was also then told what a creepypasta was. I ridiculed myself because slenderman was just an internet bogeyman. But now, im just gonna see this movie, as a reminder of all the time i spent thinking about him, almost makes me nostalgic.  Thanks for jack shit slenderman, you quite litterally ruined my chidlhood.

text: Damn, I had some hope it would be good, but this doesn't look promising. If you want to tackle slenderman, you have to do it subtly. It can't be like a normal movie monster/ghost that attacks people and whatnot. Slenderman has always been scary because no one knows what he is or what he wants. The mystery is the real power here, not scary tentacles and teleporting. Ambiguity, mystery, and the quiet moments where you could contemplate on them were what really made the games creepy, and to throw that out the window is to throw the slenderman himself out of his own movie.

text: I seriously don't care if this is good or bad (although having Sony as part of it might ruin it), I'm just happy to see Slenderman on the big screen and not on some boring documentary.  And for those complaining about it being "generic", Slenderman doesn't have that much of a plot to go off of, he kidnaps people and they try to stop him, that's the acceptable and only sort of plot the Slenderman series has, and it seriously doesn't matter if it's "years late".  And also for those that are not going to see it because of how it looks and that it's being made by Sony, just give it a chance, you never know how they could possibly blow you away with this if it becomes a success, and Slenderman fans will probably love it. And the actors are giving it all they have, including the incredible Javier Botet, who has been quite popular and successful at pleasing movie fans with his monstrous roles, give them the credit they deserve.

text: You know, when I think Slender Man I think Titties and hard core violence with plenty of cursing. Scrolling through and I see so many complaints about this being PG-13. You do know there's been plenty of good horror movies that weren't R, right? Poltergeist comes to mind. Even stuff as recent as Insidious wasn't R and was pretty decent.  Though this will probably suck, it won't be because it's PG-13, it's going to be because it's the product of an uncaring industry who don't understand what made the source material work...Of course, if everyone's clamoring for a Hard R Slender Man movie, maybe the audience doesn't know either.

text: I DON'T EVEN KNOW HOW TO FEEL ABOUT THIS Like, I've always been fascinated with the concept of Slenderman. When the game the Eight Pages was released, (when I first found out about the creepypasta), I was intrigued yet terrified. I still like the concept of the thing, but it's circulating around the internet for years - and I gotta say it's really overdone. The fact that this movie  being released _now_ is a little dumb, but I don't know, I've always been interested in the different interpretations of Slenderman, so I am tiny bit curious about this movie.  It's most likely going to be average, maybe even generic... But if it is, then that's a shame. It's an internet legend that has grown for years, so for it to be any less than good will be dissapointing.

text: Slender man was one of my biggest childhood fears. I was so scared that some nights I wouldn't sleep at all and some nights I fell asleep with my lamp on. When I turned twelve I thought I wasn't afraid of him anymore and I started sleeping with my lamp off, but one night I heard this weird slime gurgley noise. I turned on my lamp and nothing was there so I turned it off again and I heard a deafening scream. I turned on my lamp immediately and my hands were shaking like crazy. I saw a weird greasy like tentacle looking thing pull my closet door open and the more it opened the more I could see him until it fully opened and I saw that terrifying white face and as soon as we made she contact, my lamp light bulb broke. I'm still waiting for his next return.

text: While this doesn’t look HORRIBLE, I can already tell that this is just basically throwing money at an internet meme and hoping it’ll be successful.   Stealing elements from nightmare on elm street, the ring, and just about every other cliche horror movie trope in the book.  Cabin in the woods was absolutely right. This shit gets super old.  A quiet place was the first good scary monster movie in a long time — why? Because it strived to NOT be dependent on old tricks, smoke, and mirrors.  Sony, start hiring some good writers and you’ll stop hemorrhaging money :)

text: People, why complain about this being a horrible film. This is actually pretty good for what it is. Yes, it's created by Sony and it's six years late. Booo hooo! Who the f*ck cares about that. We knew this movie was coming, yet you still complain about it being late anyway. Yes Sony created it and filmed it, but honestly this movie wasn't as bad as Goosebumps or The Conjuring, they were terrible, like lullaby stories you read to your children (not that you would). Slender Man is actually good for what it is. Have a bit of salt on it and realize this. SlenderMan is a "fictional" supernatural character, who is a thin, tall Man wearing a suit and has no face, and even has long tentacles. SlenderMan traumatizes, terrorizes and kidnaps his victims, favouring small children but goes for teenagers in this movie as well. He's like an illusion and able to make his victims, once they've looked  at his face, do terrible things. He can torment that, make them see things, give them suicidal thoughts. The more they fear him, the more he is able to control their minds until they commit suicide or get captured. This is exactly what the movie showed here. Ya'll are so hypocritical internet absorbed about how "bad" it is, it's ridiculous. Nothing stood out in this movie and they didn't add in the seven pages because of copyright from the game, but it is what it is, and it wasn't good, but it wasn't bad either.

text: Here is my theory on why a lot of people seem to hate this movie. It would appear to me, that most of perhaps all of the people saying it is bad or trash have played the Slender man game. Thus expecting the movie to follow the game. However let me interject by asking. When has any movie based off of a video game, been good compared to the game and it's plot? So far as I am aware... never. Thus I believe it's best to realize that these films are "based" and quite loosely at that. Off of the original material. I haven't seen the film yet. But I believe it'd be best to watch it with an open and unfiltered mind set that doesn't focus on what happened in the game......
